article.headline: Drake 75, Lincoln, MO 50
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa -- Drake went on a 22-5 run over the last 9:46 of the game to beat Lincoln University of Missouri 75-50 on Wednesday. Josh Parker had six 3-pointers and 22 points to lead the Bulldogs (6-2). He was joined in double figures by Josh Young with 12 points and Jonathan Cox with 11 points and eight rebounds. Parker was 6-for-9 from 3-point range and Drake made 14 of 35 3-point tries. The Bulldogs shot 50 percent and outrebounded the Blue Tigers 38-28. Lincoln (3-4) was led by Kyle Wilde with 15 points. His 3-pointer with 11:44 left pulled Lincoln within Lincoln 53-45. After two scoreless minutes, the Bulldogs began their game-clinching run, scoring 17 of the next 19 points. Joe Hutchinson had 12 points and Michael Dorton grabbed 10 rebounds for the Blue Tigers.
